## Conversation
PR 3/4 of the Google ADK stack: integration tests + test plumbing. The user
left a Conductor comment on package.json asking "why do you need lodash?" —
answered here: @google/adk's CJS build does require("lodash-es") (ESM-only,
fine on Node>=22 require(esm), fatal under jest), so the default jest
project maps lodash-es -> its CJS twin lodash, now pinned as an explicit
devDependency instead of relying on a hoisted transitive copy. The weave SDK
itself does not use lodash. See PR 1/4 note for full session context.

## Actions
Added @google/adk@^1.2.0 devDependency (npm; repo has no committed lockfile
— package-lock.json was deliberately removed in PR #6802, keep it
untracked). Wrote googleAdk.test.ts: real-runner tests (InMemoryRunner +
ScriptedLlm subclassing BaseLlm) for tool flow, SequentialAgent nesting,
model-error capture, auto-registration; direct-drive tests for streaming
partials, tool error + late afterToolCallback, out-of-tree agent parenting,
afterRun cleanup, no-client safety; plus the genai exclusion test against a
fake GoogleGenAI export.

## Errors & Mistakes
- Suite initially failed to load @google/adk under jest: lodash-es is
  ESM-only ("Unexpected token 'export'"). Fixed with the moduleNameMapper.
- The auto-instrumentation test originally relied on the real CJS require
  hook firing inside jest — it cannot: jest's module registry bypasses
  Module.prototype.require entirely. Test now applies commonPatchGoogleADK
  directly; real loader paths were verified in e2e host runs (CJS require
  and node --import=weave/instrument ESM) against prod Weave.
- zod versions aligned by luck and check: weave devDeps zod ^4.4.3,
  @google/adk needs ^4.2.1, npm hoists one copy.

## Dead Ends
- Considered NOT adding the @google/adk devDependency (duck-typed plugin
  needs nothing at runtime) and testing with hand-built fakes only. Rejected:
  a fake-driven test would never have caught that ADK 1.2.0 doesn't dispatch
  plugin agent callbacks — the real-runner tests exist precisely to pin
  ADK's actual dispatch behavior.
- jest transformIgnorePatterns + transforming lodash-es: heavier and slower
  than the one-line CJS-twin mapping.

## Hints for Future Agents
- Real loader-hook behavior can only be tested in the hostApps jest project
  (spawned node processes) or e2e; never assert require-hook effects inside
  default-project jest tests.
- ADK INFO-logs every event to the console in tests; harmless noise.
- If @google/adk ever stops requiring lodash-es, the mapping and the lodash
  devDependency can both be removed.

## Codebase Discoveries
- inMemoryTraceServer.getCalls + initWithCustomTraceServer (clientMock.ts)
  are the standard harness for integration tests; no fake TraceServer
  needed.

